tspan.tspan: VISUALIZATION
GRAPH
Algorithm for removing a single toplevel node from the group drawn
from the green circle
(logical dependencies:algorithm step label) algorithm step description
(a) Call the node to remove R.
(a:b) Attempt to traverse a path of blue edges beginning at G. Traverse
to R. Traverse one more blue edge. Call the number of edges traversed
N.
(b:c) If the traversal was successful, call the node at the end of the
traversal T. Otherwise, return a message to the caller that R is not
present in the toplevel.
(a) Call the number of nodes to remove N.
(b) Call the green node G.
(c) Insert a node. Call the node Gnew.
(ab:d) Attempt to traverse a path of N blue edges beginning at G.
(d:e) If the traversal was successful, call the node at the end of the
traversal T. Otherwise, return a message to the caller that N was too
large.
(ce:f) Insert a blue edge from Gnew to T.
(bc:g) Insert a green edge from Gnew to G.
(fg:h) Switch the green node to Gnew.
RUNTIME: O(N) (because of the traversal)
